(18, 4, 'Moving to Switzerland: All that you need to know', 'moving-to-switzerland-all-that-you-need-to-know', 'blogs/IC6KpRhjDSOgCoPpVbCdZRIRbIyotOHZqNST9NCM.jpg', '<p>Embarking on a <a href=\"https://easymoveeurope.com/\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">house removal to Switzerland</span></a> can be both exhilarating and overwhelming. With its breathtaking landscapes and vibrant culture, Switzerland offers an enticing destination for a fresh start. However, a successful relocation requires meticulous planning and reliable assistance. In this comprehensive guide, we&#39;ll take you through the essential steps of a stress-free house removal to Switzerland, and why <a href=\"https://easymoveeurope.com\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">hiring a van with a driver</span></a> from Easy Move Europe is the smart choice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: Research and Plan Ahead -&nbsp;Preparing the documentation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start by conducting thorough research on Switzerland&#39;s customs regulations, residency requirements, and transportation options. Create a detailed moving checklist to keep track of tasks and deadlines. By planning ahead, you can avoid last-minute stress and ensure a smooth transition to your new Swiss home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are moving from any EU to Switzerland, in general, you don&rsquo;t have to pay any taxes but the country has some requirements that need to follow up, such provide a list of documentation:<br />\r\n- Copy of ID;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Proof of residence, proving that you have resided in Europe (country of origin) for a minimum period of 6 months;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Proof that you have a visa to reside in Switzerland (except for Switzerland citizens);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Listed of the items with their value (be careful to not overestimate your goods, as you can be taxed by the border control);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- <a href=\"https://www.bazg.admin.ch/bazg/en/home/information-individuals/personal-property--students--holiday-homes--getting-married